The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	New Delhi, April 13 (PTI): Indian Muslim League MP Abdul Wahab, accused of using foul language against an Air India pilot, has refused to apologise.          
	The Indian Commercial Pilots Association had said it would file a defamation suit against Wahab. On the charge that he had created a security scare by entering the cockpit, Wahab said he would write to the civil aviation minister to install cameras inside cockpits to show people what happens there.                  
	Chandigarh (PTI): Former Pakistan minister and human rights activist Ansar Burney has said India and Pakistan should do away with visas. This will facilitate unrestricted movement of people and normalise ties faster.                   
	New Delhi (PTI): A mentally challenged girl who can neither speak nor hear has allegedly been raped by a bus driver known to her family. Sandeep Rawat, 27, a mini-bus driver, raped the 12-year-old on on Saturday night when her grandmother was taking the girl to the bathroom outside their house, a police officer said.                   
	Shimla (PTI): Himachal Pradesh has requested the Centre to lift the ban on export of monkeys, saying the animals are a menace to farmers. Pressure from animal rights activists, including former Union minister Maneka Gandhi, had forced the Centre to clamp a country-wide ban on the export of monkeys in 1982.                   
	 Dubai (PTI): Over 2,000 striking Indian construction workers in Bahrain have agreed to return to work after being promised a pay hike. An Indian embassy official said they could not interfere unless the workers filed a complaint with them.                   
	Srinagar (PTI): A mob killed a leopard on Saturday, sources said. The leopard had ventured into a village and attacked people in panic, injuring six. It was chased and killed by the mob with lathis and sharp weapons.                                                                                                                         
